{
  "texts": [
    "SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) was used to interpret the final RF models and quantify the contribution of each selected vegetation index to the predictions.",
    "In addition, out-of-fold (OOF) test predictions were collected by aggregating the predicted values from all test folds, enabling an overall out-of-fold evaluation of model performance.",
    "The second state estimation model selected for analysis was a DL vision transformer (ViT) using multi-task learning to predict all RVs simultaneously.",
    "ViT was selected for its reputation as both a state-of-the art computer vision approach and a highly complex model that has not been widely explored for use in nutrient state estimation 57 but shows promise for precision agriculture.",
    "58 It was also selected over more commonly deployed architectures such as convolutional neural networks (CNN) like ResNet 59 due to ViT's ability to make use of spatial and spectral relationships using self-attention mechanisms."
  ]
}